<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 03 at 2:10PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
northeastern Alleghany and southern Bath Counties in west central
Virginia through 245 PM EDT...
At 210 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Nimrod Hall, or near Millboro, moving southwest at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Clifton Forge...
Warm Springs...
Millboro...
Hot Springs...
Iron Gate...
Lake Moomaw...
and Douthat State Park.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
